{
  "text": "The incidence of clinical height loss, defined as at least 1.5 inches changes from time of randomization, was investigated with a Cox proportional hazards model that was stratified on age group and randomization into the dietary trial and hormone therapy trials. (Clinical guidelines state that historical height loss of 1.5 inches [3.8 cm] among postmenopausal women age 50 and older constitutes the need for further evaluation for vertebral fractures. [CITATION_1] ) The Grambsch and Therneau test did not suggest any evidence against the proportionality assumption (P \u00bc 0.65).",
